**Tests:**
- Legacy YAML (no `retros:` block) ΓÁÈ `w.Retros == nil`, `w.OnRunCloseEnabled() == true`, all other trigger accessors false, no validation error.
- `ParseYAML(legacy).YAML()` round-trips BYTE-STABLE: re-encoding a legacy workflow.yaml that has no `retros:` produces NO spurious `retros:` block (assert bytes equal input / assert no "retros" substring).
- `retros:` block PRESENT with `on_run_close` omitted ΓÁÈ `w.Retros != nil` (presence preserved) AND `w.OnRunCloseEnabled() == true` (effective default).
- Explicit `on_run_close: false` honored ΓÁÈ `w.OnRunCloseEnabled() == false`.
- Automated-trigger-without-generator ΓÁÈ ErrInvalidWorkflow, but ONLY for an explicit block (e.g. block with `on_failed_verify: true` and no generator errors; an ABSENT block never errors even though on_run_close is effectively true).
- `on_repeated_gate_block.enabled: true`, threshold omitted ΓÁÈ `w.RepeatedGateBlockThreshold() == 3`, valid; threshold `0` ΓÁÈ error; threshold `>= 1` ΓÁÈ valid.
- KnownFields rejects an unknown key inside `retros:` AND inside nested `on_repeated_gate_block:`.
- `Default().YAML()` golden bytes UNCHANGED (existing test still passes ΓÇõ `Default()` leaves `Retros == nil`, omitted).
- Explicit-block round-trip stable: parseΓÁÈencodeΓÁÈparse of an authored block (with some fields set, some omitted) yields an equal struct and equal bytes (omitted fields stay omitted).
- Manual-only / all-automated-off explicit block: a present block with `on_run_close: false` and every other trigger false ΓÁÈ no generator required (no error).

