**Risks:** Low. Additive, optional field following the existing `Eval *Eval` optional-pointer convention. The accessor model removes the round-trip and presence-bit hazards of the earlier synthesize-on-absent approach: `Retros == nil` Γçõ absent, defaults are computed on read, the struct is never mutated, so legacy YAML re-encodes byte-stable and the generator-required rule is correctly gated on an explicit block. No consumers break: the only external readers are internal/cli/init.go (uses Default()/ParseYAML; Default() leaves Retros nil) ΓÇõ adding an optional field + read accessors is backward compatible.

**Gate tier:** Tier 1. The review-gate runbook (docs/plans/dogfood/review-gate-runbook.md:25) lists "workflow ... schema/format ... changes" as a Tier 1 trigger. Although this change is additive + optional + advisory (no gating, no storage write), it modifies the workflow schema and future compatibility of .etude/workflow.yaml, which is squarely the runbook's letter. Recommend Tier 1; the gate holds the runbook's text.

